🔥 GroupDefinition kya hota hai?
👉 GroupDefinition = ek rule/definition hoti hai jisse group dynamically banta hai
👉 Matlab:-
“Kaun log group me aayenge — ye condition define karta hai”
one line:-
GroupDefinition ek dynamic rule-based group hota hai jo filter ke basis pe users ko automatically include karta hai.

🧠 Simple Example:-
Group Name: India_Employees
Rule:-
country = India
👉 Jo bhi user ka country = India
👉 Wo automatically group me aa jayega 🔥

🔥 Static vs Dynamic Group:-
Type	            Kaise banta
Static Group:------manually add
GroupDefinition:---rule se auto

🔥 GroupDefinition me kya hota hai?
👉 Ye cheeze hoti hain:-
Name
Description
Filter / Rule
Application
Owner
Attributes

1️⃣ Name Methods:-
getName()
setName(String name)
👉 Group ka naam set/get karta hai

2️⃣ Description:-
getDescription()
setDescription(String description)
👉 Group ka detail

3️⃣ Filter / Population (MOST IMPORTANT 🔥)
getFilter()
setFilter(Filter filter)
👉 Ye decide karta hai:-
kaun group me aayega

💻 Example:-
Filter filter = Filter.eq("country", "India");
groupDef.setFilter(filter);

4️⃣ Application:-
getApplication()
setApplication(Application app)
👉 Kis system ka group hai.

4️⃣ Application:-
getApplication()
setApplication(Application app)
👉 Kis system ka group hai.

6️⃣ Attributes:-
getAttributes()
setAttributes(Attributes attrs)
👉 Extra data store karta hai

7️⃣ Created / Modified:-
getCreated()
getModified()
👉 kab bana / update hua

8️⃣ ID:-
getId()
setId(String id)
👉 unique identifier

9️⃣ toString():-
toString()
👉 object print karta hai

🔟 equals() & hashCode():-
equals(Object obj)
hashCode()
👉 compare aur hashing
----------------------------------------------------------------
5️⃣ Owner:-
getOwner()
setOwner(Identity owner)
👉 Group ka owner kaun hai
👉 Owner = wo banda (Identity) jo us group ka zimmedar hota hai,
Matlab: “Is group ka boss / responsible person”

🔥 Owner kya kya karta hai (real system)
1️⃣ Approval:-
👉 User Group / Role / Entitlement / Access request karta hai
aur owner approve ya reject karega.

2️⃣ Governance / Audit:-
Audit me pucha jayega:-
"Is group ka owner kaun hai?"

3️⃣ Certification
👉 Access review ke time:
Owner bolega:
✔️ ye user rehna chahiye
❌ hata do

4️⃣ Responsibility
👉 Agar kuch galat hua:
Blame → Owner 😅
---------------------------------------------
🔥 User kya request karta hai?
👉 User Group / Role / Entitlement / Access request karta hai

🎯 Example (Group case):-
User: Ramesh
Request: India_Employees group join karna hai
👉 Matlab:-
“Mujhe is group ka member bana do”

🔥 Flow ka breakdown:-
🧠 Step 1️⃣ User request karta hai
User portal me jaata hai
↓
Search karta hai: India_Employees
↓
Click: Request Access

🧠 Step 2️⃣ System check karta hai
Kya group requestable hai?
Kya policy allow karti hai?

🧠 Step 3️⃣ Owner ke paas jata hai
Request → Group Owner
👉 Owner decide karega:-
✔️ Approve
❌ Reject

🧠 Step 4️⃣ Agar approve hua
User → group me add ho jayega
----------------------------------------------------------------
()groupdefinition me Role / Entitlement / Access request ka matlab ?
---
🔥 Sabse pehle clear kar le:-
👉 User direct “GroupDefinition” ko request nahi karta ❌
👉 User actually request karta hai:-
Role
Entitlement
Access
👉 GroupDefinition bas backend me decide karta hai ki user automatically group me aaye ya nahi ✅

🔥 Example:-
User: Amit
Request: Developer Role

👉 Role me kya hai:-
Department = IT set ho gaya

👉 GroupDefinition:-
If department = IT → IT_Group

👉 Final:-
Amit → IT_Group me auto add 🔥
----------------------------------------------------
👉 “Agar user group me aa jaye toh kya usko group ke entitlements mil jate hain?”

🔥 1️⃣ Case: Group → Entitlement mapping hai,
👉 Agar group ke andar entitlements defined hain

🎯 Example:-
Group: IT_Group

Entitlements:-
- DB_READ
- SERVER_ACCESS

👉 Agar user group me add hua:-
User → IT_Group

👉 To automatically:-
User → DB_READ ✅
User → SERVER_ACCESS ✅
👉 🔥 YES mil gaya
-------------------------------------------------
🔥 2️⃣ Case: Group sirf grouping ke liye hai:-
👉 Kabhi group sirf UI/filter ke liye hota hai

Group: India_Employees
(no entitlement mapping)

👉 User group me aaya:-
User → India_Employees

👉 But:-
No access ❌
---------------------------------------------------------
🔥 3️⃣ Case: Group → Role → Entitlement:-
👉 Real system me mostly indirect flow hota hai

🎯 Example:-
Group: IT_Group
        ↓
Role: Developer
        ↓
Entitlements:
- DB_READ
- GIT_ACCESS

👉 Flow:-
User → Group
        ↓
Role assign
        ↓
Entitlements milte hain 🔥
-------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 4️⃣ GroupDefinition wala case:-
👉 Agar user auto group me aaya:-
Rule: department = IT
👉 User IT hai → group me add
👉 Phir:-
✔️ Agar mapping hai → access milega
❌ Nahi hai → nahi milega
------------------------------------------------------------
GroupDefinition group = new GroupDefinition();

// Name
group.setName("IT_Group");

// Description
group.setDescription("All IT employees");

// Filter (RULE 🔥)
Filter filter = Filter.eq("department", "IT");

// Apply rule
group.setFilter(filter);

// Save (context me)
context.saveObject(group);
context.commitTransaction();